description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated and enthusiastic Senior Pharmacy Technician to join our friendly team. The post holder will manage the Rotational Distribution Lead, Pharmacy Invoice Administrator and a team of Pharmacy Assistants and Pharmacy Messengers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be able to enhance existing skills and given opportunities to develop new skills Key elements of the role are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To provide an efficient service within the stores and distribution department supporting the Distribution lead&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To manage the rotational procurement technician ensuring stock is ordered in a timely manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role offers an exciting opportunity to be able to significantly contribute to medicines optimisation, patient experience, pharmacy performance and support the department and Trust objectives. We are therefore looking for a committed GPhC registered Pharmacy Technician who will contribute to our ongoing success. You will work as part of a friendly and supportive team of Technicians, Assistants, Administrators and Pharmacists&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Name Rosemary Vambe Job title Pharmacy Purchasing, Homecare and IPP Team Manager Email address rosemary.vambe@gosh.nhs.uk Telephone number 0207 405 9200 Ext: 5336&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OR Karen Matthews - karen.matthews@gosh.nhs.uk&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
